{% extends 'learn/subtopic.html.j2' %}
{% block explanation %}
  <p>A function with a polynomial in its denominator can be decomposed into <a href="{{ url_for('learn.topic', topic_id='partial_fractions') }}">partial fractions</a> to make it easier to integrate. For example:</p>
  <p class="math">$$
    \text{Evaluate } \int\frac{3x - 2}{x^2 - 2x - 6} dx.
  $$</p>
  <p>The first step is to decompose \(\frac{3x - 2}{x^2 - 2x - 6}\) into partial fractions.</p>
  <p class="math">$$
    \begin{eqnarray}
      \frac{3x - 2}{x^2 - 2x - 6} &amp;=&amp; \frac{3x - 2}{(x + 2)(x - 4)} \\
      \frac{3x - 2}{(x + 2)(x - 4)} &amp;=&amp; \frac{A}{x + 2} + \frac{B}{x - 4} \\
      3x - 2 &amp;=&amp; A(x - 4) + B(x + 2) \\
      3x - 2 &amp;=&amp; Ax - 4A + Bx + 2B \\
      3x - 2 &amp;=&amp; (A + B)x + (-4A + 2B) \\
      \\
      A + B &amp;=&amp; 3 \\
      -4A + 2B &amp;=&amp; -2 \\
      \\
      A &amp;=&amp; \frac{4}{3} \\
      B &amp;=&amp; \frac{5}{3} \\
      \\
      \frac{3x - 2}{x^2 - 2x - 6} &amp;=&amp; \frac{4}{3(x + 2)} + \frac{5}{3(x - 4)} \\
    \end{eqnarray}
  $$</p>
  <p>The function can now be integrated easily.</p>
  <p class="math">$$
    \begin{eqnarray}
      \int\frac{3x - 2}{x^2 - 2x - 6} dx &amp;=&amp; \int (\frac{4}{3(x + 2)} + \frac{5}{3(x - 4)}) dx \\
      &amp;=&amp; \frac{4}{3}\int\frac{1}{x + 2} dx + \frac{5}{3}\int\frac{1}{x - 4} dx \\
      &amp;=&amp; \underline{\underline{\frac{4}{3}ln|x + 2| + \frac{5}{3}ln|x - 4| + c}}
    \end{eqnarray}
  $$</p>


{% endblock explanation %}
